Added test to verify enabling SSH via GUI
No need to create new one. These are already there in gui/data/gui_variables.py
Verify that SSH to BMC starts working after enabling SSH.
Instead of sleep, refresh until GUI reflects disable SSH.
Instead of this, check if xpath_bmc_ssh_value contains Enabled
Wait Until Key Word Succeeds   Verify SSH Login
Verify SSH login and command execution on SSH session.

Comments not required as documentation talks about it.
    Open Connection And Login
    BMC Execute Command  /sbin/ip addr

Keep space and end comment with a period "."

    # Disable SSH via Redfish.

Better to check if element contains enable status.
Wait Until Element Contain  ${xpath_bmc_ssh_value}  Enabled  timeout=10

Correction:

Better to check if element contains disabled SSH status.
Wait Until Element Contain  ${xpath_bmc_ssh_value}  Disabled  timeout=10
I tried this, but it's not working. So I kept previous one, any changes kindly let me know.

That should have worked. If its not working then there is some problem with XPath. May be just use //*[@data-test-id='policies-toggle-bmcShell']/following-sibling::label as XPath would fix the problem.

We can try like this xpath and avoid using "Click Element At Coordinates" keyword.

Click Element  ${xpath_bmc_ssh_toggle}

*** Variables ***
${xpath_bmc_ssh_toggle}       //*[@data-test-id='policies-toggle-bmcShell']//following-sibling::label

Missed observing last time. As we want to make sure that SSH login happens we can just try like this and skip creating new keyword - Verify SSH Login.

Wait Until Keyword Succeeds  1 min  5 sec  Open Connection And Login
here for cross verifying purpose i.e, whether after ssh login command works or not i have used this keyword...if it's not required kindly let me know will modify
Not required. Please make changes as suggested.
Move this keyword at common place so that others can also use it - gui/lib/gui_resource.robot

This should be either part of the teardown or suite teardown. 

The idea behind is if the disable via redfish succeeded but the verification failed, the SSH would be blocked on the system and subsequent any SSH related would be blocked including FFDC data over SSH

Make sense. We can add something like below in teardown

    [Teardown]  Run Keywords  Redfish.Patch  /redfish/v1/Managers/bmc/NetworkProtocol
    ...  body={"SSH":{"ProtocolEnabled":True}}  valid_status_codes=[200, 204]  AND
    ...  Wait Until Keyword Succeeds  1 min  5 sec  Open Connection And Login
Done  : added this as a part of teardown also.
One of these should be fine here. Any particular reason for having these two status code?
